Method Detail

nextNonDescendantNode

public Node nextNonDescendantNode()
Return the next non-descendant Node (which may or may not be a sibling node) or null if none exists. For Attribute nodes, this method returns null.

nextSiblingNode

public Node nextSiblingNode()
Return the next sibling Node (ie, the next Node that has the same parent) or null if none exists. For Attribute nodes, this method returns null.

isBetween

Whether or not this node occurs in the range between the specified startNode and endNode, inclusive of the start and end nodes.

Parameters:
startNode - lower bound node, or null for no lower bound.
endNode - upper bound node, or null for no upper bound.

isBetween

public boolean isBetween(Node startNode,
                         Node endNode,
                         boolean inclusive)
Whether or not this node occurs in the range between the specified startNode and endNode, inclusivity as specified.

Parameters:
startNode - lower bound node, or null for no lower bound.
endNode - upper bound node, or null for no upper bound.
inclusive - whether the range is inclusive of the startNode and endNode.
